    <section class="section" id="ch1">
      <span class="chapter-label">Chapter 1</span>
      <h2>🧬 What Are Peptides?</h2>
      <p class="chapter-sub"><em>In the beginning, there were amino acids</em></p>
      <p>Before we talk about buying, mixing, or dosing anything, let's start where every good sermon should — at the beginning. What actually is a peptide?</p>
      <p>Strip away the mystique and it's simple: a peptide is a short chain of amino acids — the same building blocks your body uses to make every protein you're made of — linked together in a specific sequence. Your body already makes thousands of them. They're how your cells talk to each other: telling tissue to repair itself, telling glands to release hormones, telling your immune system when to stand up and fight. A synthetic peptide is just a precision copy of that same language, built to say one specific thing to one specific receptor.</p>
      <p>That precision is what sets peptides apart from a typical pill bottle:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Specificity:</strong> Most peptides lock onto one target with real precision instead of carpet-bombing your whole system the way a lot of conventional drugs do — a big part of why the side-effect profile tends to be gentler.</li>
        <li><strong>Efficiency:</strong> Because they're doing a job your body already knows how to do, tiny doses go a long way. We're talking micrograms, not milligrams, for a lot of these.</li>
        <li><strong>Biocompatibility:</strong> Your body isn't fighting off a foreign invader. Peptides are built from the same amino acid alphabet you already run on, so they tend to be well tolerated and get metabolized and cleared the way your own proteins do.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>None of that makes them risk-free — they're still potent biological signals, and potent things deserve respect. Source quality matters enormously (more on that in a few chapters), and anything you're doing is better done alongside a healthcare provider who actually knows this space, not just a search engine and a prayer.</p>
      <div class="commandment">Peptides aren't magic. They're just your body's own language, spoken more precisely.</div>
      <p>That's the whole foundation. Everything else in this guide — the mixing, the dosing, the vendors, the whole gray market of it — is just logistics sitting on top of that one idea. Let's get into it.</p>
    </section>

