    <section class="section" id="ch3">
      <span class="chapter-label">Chapter 3</span>
      <h2>🧪 Yes, You Have to Mix Them</h2>
      <p class="chapter-sub"><em>On the sacred art of reconstitution</em></p>
      <p>I know. You didn't sign up for chemistry class. But hear me, friend — it's easier than it sounds, and after the first couple of times, it becomes second nature.</p>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>Draw <strong>BAC water</strong> into a syringe</li>
        <li>Gently inject it into your <strong>peptide vial</strong></li>
        <li>Swirl slowly — do <strong>not</strong> shake like a cocktail</li>
        <li>Let it dissolve for a few minutes</li>
        <li>Store in the fridge, away from light (a small jar works great)</li>
      </ol>
      <p>This process is called <strong>reconstitution</strong> — just a fancy word for mixing. <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=APpVFoU3GlU" target="_blank">Here's a helpful video walkthrough.</a> Want the deeper study on this? See <a href="/guides/reconstitution-solutions">Reconstitution Solutions</a> and <a href="/guides/reconstituting-a-vial">Reconstituting a Vial</a> in the Gray Market.</p>
      <p>The congregation has spoken: the first mix is the hardest. After that, it's as routine as your morning coffee.</p>
